<h1>Problem 943 - 2016 IMOSL, G5, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Let \(D\) be the foot of perpendicular from \(A\) to the Euler line (the line passing through the circumcentre and the orthocentre) of an acute scalene triangle \(ABC\). A circle \(\omega\) with centre \(S\) passes through \(A\) and \(D\), and it intersects sides \(AB\) and \(AC\) at \(X\) and \(Y\) respectively. Let \(P\) be the foot of altitude from \(A\) to \(BC\), and let \(M\) be the midpoint of \(BC\). Prove that the circumcentre of triangle \(XSY\) is equidistant from \(P\) and \(M\).</p>
